<span class="displaytext">arlington, va -- u.s. senator (candidate full)'s presidential campaign today released the following statement on behalf of (PARTY NAME) members from ohio's congressional delegation who applauded (candidate full)'s decisive primary election victory in the buckeye state. <p>ohio's importance in the national electoral landscape is well-documented, and (candidate full) has quickly galvanized strong support among some of ohio's most influential (PARTY NAME)s in washington. the members, whose districts range from moderate to conservative, have embraced (candidate full) for his consistent adherence to the principles that matter most to all (PARTY NAME)s -- most notably, his commitment to national defense and the war against islamic extremism, and his relentless drive to balance the budget and control federal spending. </p><p>with (candidate full)'s lock on the (PARTY NAME) nomination all but secured, members from the ohio delegation reaffirmed their unequivocal support for (candidate full)'s candidacy, and issued the following statements: <b> </b></p><p>senator george voinovich:<br/>"ohioans have spoken, and i'm confident that (candidate full) will be our nominee and our next president. in times like these, america needs a strong leader with experience, and that's (candidate full)." <b> </b></p><p>john boehner (oh-8):<br/>"senator (candidate last) is a tested leader who will fight wasteful spending and needless tax hikes, keep america secure, and nominate judges who understand that courts should not be legislating from the bench. americans know he is a man of great character and integrity, and trust him to take on the many opportunities and challenges of the years ahead. (candidate full) understands washington is broken; together i believe we can fix it." <b> </b></p><p>ralph regula (oh-16):<br/>"if you reduced the country down to one state, you'd probably be left with ohio, so this is an important win for senator (candidate last). we've seen from tonight's results that senator (candidate last)'s strong record and vision for expanding job opportunity and economic growth, keeping our homeland safe and controlling government spending are what the voters in ohio are seeking and what i believe the country will look for in the fall." <b> </b></p><p>deborah pryce (oh-15):<br/>"ohio is the epicenter of the electoral map, and senator (candidate last)'s support here is robust, energized and diverse. voters will have the choice between two dramatically different candidates and visions in november, and senator (candidate last)'s courage, experience, and conviction will prove to be the decisive difference for ohioans." <b> </b></p><p>steve chabot (oh-1): <br/>"i commend senator (candidate last) on his victory tonight in ohio. over the years he has proven himself to be a man of great courage and he has worked to build the necessary experience to lead this country." <b> </b></p><p>steven latourette (oh-14):<br/>"(candidate full)'s solid victories in ohio and texas tonight cement the nomination and will now free him to define the issues that make him a better choice for america." <b> </b></p><p>pat tiberi (oh-12):<br/>"i am pleased ohioans agreed that (candidate full) is a solid leader. his fiscal policy -- to spend taxpayers dollars responsibly, eliminate waste, and lower taxes, puts families' priorities ahead of increased government spending. i am proud that ohioans have helped move (candidate full) further toward the nomination." <b> </b></p><p>michael turner (oh-3):<br/>"ohioans made a clear choice tonight. our vote for (candidate full) for president was a vote for job creation and a strong national defense. i look forward to working with senator (candidate last) toward victory in november." <b> </b></p><p>jean schmidt (oh-2):<br/>"(candidate full) is a strong fiscal conservative and an ardent defender of life. he is a true american hero and i am proud he is our nominee." <b> </b></p><p>bob latta (oh-5):<br/>"ohio will certainly be the center of attention this fall, and senator (candidate last)'s victory this evening is an important step toward his victory in november. ohioans are looking for a candidate who is committed to keeping our country safe and dedicated to reducing federal spending. i believe senator (candidate last) offers the working families of ohio a clear alternative as a principled leader to ensure both our country's safety and economic viability in the world marketplace."</p></span>



